Your wording is correct. I would just polish it slightly so the flow is clear and precise:

```text
This is a B2Boost post-login URL.

Flow:

1. After sales-point selection, Arthur Core redirects the browser to B2Boost with a temporary one-time code:

   https://<B2Boost-url>/post-login?code=<handoff-code-or-UUID>

2. B2Boost then calls Arthur Core server-to-server using that code:

   POST https://<arthur-core-url>/auth/handoff/exchange

   Request body:
   {
     "code": "<handoff-code-or-UUID>"
   }

3. Arthur Core validates the code. If valid, Arthur Core returns the security context to B2Boost.

Important: Arthur Core does not send the full security context in the browser redirect URL. Only the temporary code is sent through the browser.
```

One small correction: instead of “B2Boost reverts back,” use **“B2Boost calls Arthur Core server-to-server”**. That makes it clear this is not another browser redirect.
